\]Since the coordinates of $A'$ satisfy both this equation and $y=x$, it follows that $A'=(6,6)$. Similarly, line $BC$ has equation $y=-2x+12$, and $B'=(4,4)$. Thus \[
A'B'= \sqrt{(6-4)^{2}+(6-4)^{2}}= \boxed{2\sqrt{2}}.
\][asy]
